'Ideally we want to get a block of land, put a house on it, and put it in Curtis' name,' said Warren Blissett, a coach of the rising young star.

'It's the good spirit of country folk.'

The Forster Tuncurry Hawks are staging an auction on 31 July in the hope of raising tens of thousands of dollars for their embattled young star. Ray Hadley - who visited Curtis in hospital - has already signed on to host the event.

Mr Blissett said Curtis is now able to talk and his mischievous spirit is starting to return.

